The paper deals with influence maximization in social networks, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several CS sub-fields. The most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), which specifically deals with the analysis and modeling of social networks. The paper also involves optimization problems, which suggests the category cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The use of automata and model parameters indicates the category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also proposes novel approximation algorithms, which falls under the category cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the experiments involve real-world social networks, which suggests the category cs.SOC (Computational Social Science).
